# Next.js conventions

## Read before writing
- Before adding or editing a file, read 2–3 existing files of the same kind (page, API route, component, lib module).
- Match naming, import style, error response shape, and data-fetching patterns already used in this repo.

## Router and structure
- This project uses the **Pages Router** (`pages/`), not App Router.
- Business logic belongs in `lib/`; components are UI-focused.
- API routes live in `pages/api/` and must validate inputs and return structured errors.

## Components
- Default to server-compatible components (no unnecessary `"use client"`).
- Add `"use client"` only when the component needs browser APIs, hooks, or event handlers — document why in a brief comment if non-obvious.
- Do not introduce new libraries without explicit approval.

## Data fetching
- Follow existing patterns: direct Supabase client in API routes, `fetch` from pages/components where already established.
- Never expose `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` or other server secrets to client bundles.
